# ConvoView

`ConvoView` is the primary React UI component for building chat interfaces powered by Convo-Lang.

It gives you a production-ready conversation surface with support for:

- Convo-Lang prompts and templates
- message rendering
- function/tool calls
- streaming responses
- markdown
- model selection
- attachments and images
- source view editing
- suggestions
- custom renderers
- audio recording
- live voice mode
- text-to-speech response playback
- theming
- multi-panel and redirected layouts

If you want a fast way to embed a capable AI chat UI into a React or Next.js app, `ConvoView` is the main entry point.

---

## Why use ConvoView

At a high level, `ConvoView` combines three things that are usually painful to assemble by hand:

1. **A real chat UI**
   - message list
   - input
   - status indicators
   - suggestions
   - scrolling behavior
   - source/code editing mode

2. **A conversation controller**
   - manages the active conversation
   - tracks tasks and streaming state
   - handles message appends and completions
   - connects UI state to Convo-Lang execution

3. **A Convo-Lang runtime integration**
   - uses Convo-Lang prompts directly
   - supports tool/function calls naturally
   - supports variables, templates, modules, and imports
   - supports multiple model backends and endpoints

This means you can focus on the behavior of your AI product instead of wiring together:
- chat state
- request orchestration
- tool call rendering
- markdown rendering
- source editing
- media attachment logic
- voice recording and playback
- model switching
- theme management

---

## Why Convo-Lang makes ConvoView especially useful

`ConvoView` is not just a generic chat box. It is specifically designed for **Convo-Lang conversations**.

That matters because Convo-Lang gives your UI a structured prompt and execution model instead of a plain “send text to model” flow.

### Benefits of using ConvoView with Convo-Lang

- **Prompt ownership**
  - your agent logic can live in plain-text Convo-Lang
  - easier to version, inspect, review, and share

- **Built-in structure**
  - system prompts, user messages, assistant messages, functions, results, RAG, tags, variables, and transforms all map cleanly into the UI

- **Better tool/function UX**
  - tool calls and results are first-class parts of the conversation
  - they can be shown, hidden, streamed, or custom-rendered

- **Stateful prompting**
  - variables and execution state can drive how the conversation behaves over time

- **LLM portability**
  - the same prompt can work across multiple providers and models
  - `ConvoView` can optionally expose model selection directly in the UI

- **Inspectability**
  - users and developers can switch to source mode and inspect or edit the conversation source

- **Richer app patterns**
  - use render targets, component renderers, extern functions, and source mode to build more than a standard chatbot

In practice, `ConvoView` works well for:
- copilots
- customer support agents
- structured assistants
- internal tools
- AI workflows with tools/functions
- multi-modal chat
- voice-first experiences
- developer-facing prompt editors
- side-panel artifact workflows

---

